# Deploy

Run pre-deployment checks and deploy {{PROJECT_NAME}} to the specified environment.

## Usage

```
/deploy [staging|production]
```

Default: `staging`

## Pre-flight Checks

Run ALL of these. Stop and report if any fail — do not proceed to deploy.

```bash
{{CMD_TEST}}         # All tests must pass
{{CMD_TYPECHECK}}    # No type errors
{{CMD_LINT}}         # No lint errors
{{CMD_BUILD}}        # Build must succeed
```

{{EXTRA_PREFLIGHT}}
<!-- EXTRA_PREFLIGHT example: "Also run: pnpm migrate:check # verify no pending migrations" -->

## Deploy to Staging

```bash
{{CMD_DEPLOY_STAGING}}
```

Wait for: {{STAGING_SUCCESS_SIGNAL}}
<!-- Example: "Vercel deployment URL in output — open and verify /api/health returns 200" -->

Verify: `curl {{STAGING_HEALTH_URL}}`

## Deploy to Production

**Requires confirmation before proceeding.**

Confirm: "I want to deploy to production" before running:

```bash
{{CMD_DEPLOY_PROD}}
```

Wait for: {{PROD_SUCCESS_SIGNAL}}

Verify: `curl {{PROD_HEALTH_URL}}`

## Rollback

If production verify fails:

```bash
{{CMD_ROLLBACK}}
```

{{ROLLBACK_NOTE}}
<!-- Example: "Rollback reverts code only — if migration ran, contact DBA for manual rollback" -->

## Report

After deployment, output:
```
Deployed: {{PROJECT_NAME}} → [environment]
Version: [git SHA or tag]
Status: [healthy / degraded]
URL: [environment URL]
```
